# Managed in dotfiles (stow package `ssh` -> ~/.ssh/config). SSH never rewrites
# this file, so a symlink is safe. No private keys live here — keys come from the
# encrypted `ssh` / `ssh-<initials>` vault repos (see esetup). Company/client
# identities are routed PER-FOLDER by git includeIf (~/.config/git/*.inc), not by
# Host aliases here — see the `ssh` repo's ADDING_AN_IDENTITY.md.

Host *
    AddKeysToAgent yes

# Personal (kernvex) = the github.com default. Both IdentityFiles are the SAME key:
# this machine has ~/.ssh/id_ed25519; a machine bootstrapped from the `ssh` vault
# has ~/.ssh/kernvex_id_ed25519. Listing both means "use whichever exists", so this
# one config is correct on every machine. IdentitiesOnly pins these and ignores
# whatever else the agent holds, so a company key loaded in the agent can never
# hijack a personal github push.
#
# NEVER add `Host *  IdentityFile ...` — forcing one key onto every host was the
# original bug that made every push authenticate as the wrong account.
Host github.com
    User git
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/kernvex_id_ed25519
    IdentitiesOnly yes
